ZH: 我们的团队不应该排斥任何人的观点。
EN: Our team should not exclude any person's point of view.

ZH: 她对新技术抱有排斥的态度。
EN: She has a negative attitude towards new technology.

ZH: 这种偏见导致了他们之间的排斥和冲突。
EN: This bias has led to their exclusion and conflicts.

ZH: 家庭成员之间的冷漠会导致排斥感的产生。
EN: Coldness among family members can lead to feelings of exclusion.

ZH: 我们必须排斥所有形式的歧视。
EN: We must exclude all forms of discrimination.

ZH: 学校里不存在排斥的氛围，所有学生都被平等对待。
EN: There is no atmosphere of exclusion in the school, all students are treated equally.

ZH: 那个社区对外来者抱有排斥的态度。
EN: That community has a hostile attitude towards outsiders.

ZH: 公司排斥了一位经验丰富的员工，这是个错误的决定。
EN: The company excluded an experienced employee, which was a wrong decision.

ZH: 他在某种程度上排斥改变。
EN: He is resistant to change to some extent.

ZH: 拥有开放的心态可以减少人与人之间的排斥感。
EN: Having an open mindset can reduce feelings of exclusion among people.

ZH: 那个团体排斥了他们不认同的意见。
EN: The group excluded opinions that they did not agree with.

ZH: 他因为肤色而遭受社会的排斥。
EN: He faced societal exclusion because of his skin color.

ZH: 孩子们对新同学表现出了排斥的行为。
EN: The children displayed exclusionary behavior towards the new classmate.

